This paper proposes a new mechanism for demand response contracts in the energy sector, which involves designing contracts that incentivize consumers to reduce their power consumption during periods of high demand. The paper uses game theory and optimization techniques to design the mechanism, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and simulation of the mechanism, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
